[7]<a href="javascript:card_browser(233)">Anduin Wilderland</a><br>
[8]<a href="javascript:card_browser(235)">Anduin Banks</a><br>
[9]<a href="javascript:card_browser(242)">Summit of Amon Hen</a><br>
<br>
Free People (28+2) :<br>
Gandalf, Friend of Shirefolk x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(200)">Asfaloth</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(256)">Gwemegil</a>  x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(181)">Ancient Enmity</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(210)">Border Defenses</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(247)">Defiance</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(295)">Strength of Spirit</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(294)">Sleep, Caradhras</a><br>
Galadriel x2<br>
Celeborn x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(250)">Elrond, Lord of Rivendell</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(264)">The Mirror of Galadriel</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(276)">The White Arrows of Lorien</a> x3<br>
<br>
Shadow (30) :<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(72)">Goblin Runner</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(86)">Moria Scout</a>  x4<br>
Cave Troll Of Moria x3<br>
Cave Troll&#8217;s Hammer x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(91)">They Are Coming</a><br>
Troll&#8217;s Keyward<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(93)">Through the Misty Mountains</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(133)">Band of the Eye</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(151)">Orc Butchery</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(154)">Orc Inquisitor</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(165)">Tower Lieutenant</a> x4<br>
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Strategy :<br>
When i first started LOTR TCG, i tried to made a discard deck. It used Gimli, Dwarven Armor and Nobody Tosses A Dwarf. The Shadow part was composed of Sauron Orcs. But this deck wasn&#8217;t very effective : opponent has no cards but only when he reached site 9. Then, like many players i played a deck plenty of Elves and played Far Seeing Eyes and The Mirror Of Galadriel. I always had the same shadow part and it didn&#8217;t always work. This deck is my third attempt to made an effective discard deck, and this time, it&#8217;s working ! :-)<br>
<br>
Bid 2 (3 is too high versus Nazguls decks) and choose your opponent to begin. That way he&#8217;ll play on your sites. Except Rivendell Valley and Balin&#8217;s Tomb, those sites are dedicated to help your shadow part : Weathertop gives a precious 3 twilight for your roaming minions. Dimrill Dale allows you to play many Moria Orcs and the Wilderland skips the archery phase (good versus ARV).  Anduin Banks will help versus large fellowship (although it should&#8217;nt happen as we will see below).<br>
Rivendell Valley is a card drawer as you play 3 elves in your Free People part, and Balin&#8217;s Tomb is here to help healing Legolas by discarding a copy or two of The White Arrows Of Lorien (TWAOL).<br>
<br>
This deck is a heavy discard deck.<br>
Both parts of the deck are dedicated to that.<br>
<br>
Free People :<br>
Play Galadriel and her mirror, or Legolas and TWAOL as soon as you can, and make opponent suffer. <br>
Use Celeborn to heal Galadriel or Elrond (to draw more cards). Gandalf is here to play SOS, allowing Legolas to exert both for archery and TWAOL. He may also cancel conditions with Sleep, Caradhras.<br>
Arwen is there to win skirmishes and play some nasty Ancient Enmity. Boost Arwen with Asfaloth and Gwemegil. Don&#8217;t run unless you&#8217;re forced to.<br>
<br>
Shadow :<br>
This is a mix of Moria and Sauron Orcs. The default i noticed in many discard decks is that when opponent realises that you play such a deck, he often runs madly and you can&#8217;t set up your tricks. You don&#8217;t want that to happen,  of course, so you have to play powerful minions to stop him. To play Through the Misty Mountains (TMM), heavy discard condition (play multiple copies if you can), you must play Moria minions that can exert. That&#8217;s why there are only Moria Scouts (not expensive) and Cave Trolls (both powerful and exert-able). The Cave Troll will slow opponent and hopefully kill some companions, allowing you to play a nasty Orc Butchery (play it in the mid-game). <br>
Don&#8217;t keep copies of TMM after site 6.<br>
The Goblin runners will provide extra twilight for your roaming Sauron Orcs. Band Of The Eye slows the opponent and help the discard mechanics as the Inquisitors and the Tower Lieutenants do. They Are coming is here to change your Free People hand with Shadow minions.<br>
<br>
The potential amount of cards opponent may lose is amazing ! Notice that he&#8217;ll often lose his cards randomly (that&#8217;s the worse for him).<br>
<br>
You should do well versus any deck.<br>
<br>
Enjoy,<br>
<br>
Witch-King.<br>
